

Reinstall Raspberry Pi software via PI imager
making sure SPI & I2C are active: 
sudo raspi-config (-> P3; interface options) 
activate: SPI & I2C sudo reboot
Update all software: 
sudo apt update 
sudo apt upgrade 
sudo apt install python3-venv python3-pip python3-smbus i2c-tools python3-dev build-essential
Make a direction where all the needed packages will be installed: 
mkdir ~/testing 
cd ~/testing
python3 -m venv env
source env/bin/activate
Install all the packages:
python3 -m pip install spidev
pip install pygame
pip install pyrf24
sudo apt install python3-rpi-lgpio
sudo apt install build-essential python3-dev swig liblgpio-dev
(in env) pip install rpi-lgpio

pip install --no-deps adafruit-blinka adafruit-platformdetect adafruit-pureio


pip install --no-deps adafruit-circuitpython-servokit \
  adafruit-circuitpython-pca9685 \
  adafruit-circuitpython-motor \
  adafruit-circuitpython-busdevice \
  adafruit-circuitpython-register \
  Adafruit-circuitpython-typing
pip install typing-extensions --no-deps
#pip install adafruit-circuitpython-charlcd

Connecting GitHub: 
sudo apt install -y gh
gh auth login 
Go to git website (via command screen) and log in to get the code 
Fill in the code in the command screen and then 
git clone https://github.com/TijgervdD/leafy.git
Note: because it is a raspberry pi 5 the adafruit servomotor HAT software hass to be downloaded through such a way, otherwise you get a GPIO error. This is because of the software differences between pi 5 and younger Piâ€™s



##### Starting command
[Unit]
Description=My Python Project Service
After=network.target

[Service]
# Replace 'pi' with your actual username if different
User=grp2 
# The directory where your script lives
WorkingDirectory=/home/grp2/leafy
# Path to the python executable INSIDE your venv + path to your script
ExecStart=/home/grp2/codeEnv/env/bin/python /home/grp2/leafy/finalBeast.py
Restart=always
# StandardOutput and StandardError help with debugging later
StandardOutput=inherit
StandardError=inherit

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target 


#################
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable myscript.service
sudo systemctl start myscript.service

################## check if code is in start up: 
sudo systemctl status myscript.service